{2n \choose 2r}
 \begin{align*} & 2n \times (2n - 2) \times (2n - 4) \times (2n - 6) \times \cdots \times (2n - 4r + 2) \\ =& 2^{2r} \times n \times (n - 1) \times \cdots \times (n - 2r + 1) \\ =& 2^{2r} \times \frac{ n! }{ (n - 2r)! } \end{align*} 
\frac{ n! }{ (n - 2r)! } \Leftrightarrow \binom{n}{2r}
